def bootstrap_mediation(data, n_bootstraps=1000):
    indirect_effects = []
    for _ in range(n_bootstraps):
        sample = data.sample(n=len(data), replace=True)
        model2_sample = sm.OLS(sample['wd5total'], sm.add_constant(sample['wd2'])).fit()
        model3_sample = sm.OLS(sample['conscientiousness_score'], sm.add_constant(sample[['wd2', 'wd5total']])).fit()
        indirect_effect = model2_sample.params['wd2'] * model3_sample.params['wd5total']
        indirect_effects.append(indirect_effect)
    
    indirect_effects = np.array(indirect_effects)
    ci_low = np.percentile(indirect_effects, 2.5)
    ci_high = np.percentile(indirect_effects, 97.5)
    
    return indirect_effects.mean(), ci_low, ci_high

mean_indirect_effect, ci_low, ci_high = bootstrap_mediation(df)
print(f"Mean Indirect Effect: {mean_indirect_effect}")
print(f"95% CI: [{ci_low}, {ci_high}]")

def map_region(provcd):
    #  provcd 
    provcd_str = str(provcd).strip()

    return ''

#Bootstrap
def bootstrap_mediation(data, n_bootstraps=1000):
    indirect_effects = []
    
    for _ in range(n_bootstraps):
        # 
        sample = data.sample(frac=1, replace=True)
        
        # Model 1: wd2 -> wd5total
        X_mediator_sample = sample[['wd2', 'qa002', 'qb1', 'region_encoded', 'urban_encoded']]
        y_mediator_sample = sample['wd5total']
        X_mediator_sample = sm.add_constant(X_mediator_sample)
        mediator_model_1_sample = sm.OLS(y_mediator_sample, X_mediator_sample).fit()
        a = mediator_model_1_sample.params['wd2']
        
        # Model 2: wd5total -> conscientiousness_score
        X_conscientiousness_sample = sample[['wd2', 'wd5total', 'qa002', 'qb1', 'region_encoded', 'urban_encoded']]
        y_conscientiousness_sample = sample['conscientiousness_score']
        X_conscientiousness_sample = sm.add_constant(X_conscientiousness_sample)
        mediator_model_2_sample = sm.OLS(y_conscientiousness_sample, X_conscientiousness_sample).fit()
        b = mediator_model_2_sample.params['wd5total']
        
        # 
        indirect_effect = a * b
        indirect_effects.append(indirect_effect)
    
    # 95%
    ci_lower = np.percentile(indirect_effects, 2.5)
    ci_upper = np.percentile(indirect_effects, 97.5)
    
    return indirect_effects, ci_lower, ci_upper

# Bootstrap
indirect_effects, ci_lower, ci_upper = bootstrap_mediation(df)

print(f"Indirect Effect (a*b): {np.mean(indirect_effects)}")
print(f"95% Confidence Interval: [{ci_lower}, {ci_upper}]")

# CPI
cpi_df = pd.read_excel('D:/SINKY/Lecture/8001/data/CPI.xlsx')

# 20102018CPI
cpi_df = cpi_df[(cpi_df['Year'] >= 2010) & (cpi_df['Year'] <= 2018)]

# CPI
cpi_df = pd.read_excel('D:/SINKY/Lecture/8001/data/CPI.xlsx')

# 
base_year = 2010

# CPI
cpi_df['cumulative_cpi'] = cpi_df['CPI'] / cpi_df.loc[cpi_df['Year'] == base_year, 'CPI'].iloc[0]

# CPI
cumulative_cpi_dict = cpi_df.set_index('Year')['cumulative_cpi'].to_dict()

# 2018
current_year = 2018

# 
def adjust_education_spending(row):
    birth_year = current_year - row['wa1age']
    base_year_cpi = cumulative_cpi_dict.get(base_year, 1)
    birth_year_cpi = cumulative_cpi_dict.get(birth_year, 1)
    return row['wd5total'] * (base_year_cpi / birth_year_cpi)

df['wd5total_adjusted'] = df.apply(adjust_education_spending, axis=1)

def calculate_mediation_effects(df, predictor, mediator, outcome, control_vars):
    # 
    X_const = add_constant(df[[predictor] + control_vars])
    
    #  a: 
    model_a = sm.OLS(df[mediator], X_const).fit()
    path_a = model_a.params[predictor]
    
    #  b: 
    X_mediator = add_constant(df[[mediator, predictor] + control_vars])
    model_b = sm.OLS(df[outcome], X_mediator).fit()
    path_b = model_b.params[mediator]
    
    #  c': 
    X_direct = add_constant(df[[predictor, mediator] + control_vars])
    model_c_prime = sm.OLS(df[outcome], X_direct).fit()
    path_c_prime = model_c_prime.params[predictor]
    
    #  (ab)
    indirect_effect = path_a * path_b
    
    # 
    total_effect = path_a * path_b + path_c_prime
    
    return {
        'path_a': path_a,
        'path_b': path_b,
        'path_c_prime': path_c_prime,
        'indirect_effect': indirect_effect,
        'total_effect': total_effect
    }

def calculate_mediation_effects_glm(df, predictor, mediator, outcome, control_vars):
    # 
    X_const = add_constant(df[[predictor] + control_vars])
    
    #  a: 
    model_a = sm.GLM(df[mediator], X_const, family=sm.families.Gaussian()).fit()
    path_a = model_a.params[predictor]
    
    #  b: 
    X_mediator = add_constant(df[[mediator, predictor] + control_vars])
    model_b = sm.GLM(df[outcome], X_mediator, family=sm.families.Gaussian()).fit()
    path_b = model_b.params[mediator]
    
    #  c': 
    X_direct = add_constant(df[[predictor, mediator] + control_vars])
    model_c_prime = sm.GLM(df[outcome], X_direct, family=sm.families.Gaussian()).fit()
    path_c_prime = model_c_prime.params[predictor]
    
    #  (ab)
    indirect_effect = path_a * path_b
    
    # 
    total_effect = path_a * path_b + path_c_prime
    
    return {
        'path_a': path_a,
        'path_b': path_b,
        'path_c_prime': path_c_prime,
        'indirect_effect': indirect_effect,
        'total_effect': total_effect
    }

def plot_mediation_effects(results, trait):
    # 
    data = pd.DataFrame({
        'Path': ['a', 'b', 'c\'', 'Indirect (ab)', 'Total'],
        'Effect': [results['path_a'], results['path_b'], results['path_c_prime'],
                   results['indirect_effect'], results['total_effect']],
        'Legend': ['Path a', 'Path b', 'Path c\'', 'Indirect Effect (ab)', 'Total Effect']  # 
    })

    # 
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")

    # 
    plt.figure(figsize=(5, 3))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='Effect', y='Path', hue='Legend', data=data, palette=['blue', 'green', 'red', 'purple', 'orange'], legend=False)
    
    # 
    for p in ax.patches:
        width = p.get_width()
        if width >= 0:
            ax.text(width + max(results.values())*0.01, p.get_y() + p.get_height()/2., f'{width:.6f}', ha="left", va="center")  # 
        else:
            ax.text(width - max(results.values())*0.01, p.get_y() + p.get_height()/2., f'{width:.6f}', ha="right", va="center")

    # 
    plt.title(f'Mediation Effects for {trait}', fontsize=14)
    plt.xlabel('Effect Size', fontsize=12)
    plt.ylabel('Path', fontsize=12)

    # 
    plt.tight_layout()  # 
    plt.show()

# 
for trait, results in mediation_results.items():
    plot_mediation_effects(results, trait)

def plot_mediation_effects_bubble(results, trait, save_path):
    data = pd.DataFrame({
        'Path': ['a', 'b', "c'", 'Indirect (ab)', 'Total'],
        'Effect': [results['path_a'], results['path_b'], results['path_c_prime'],
                   results['indirect_effect'], results['total_effect']],
    })

    # 
    plt.figure(figsize=(5, 3))
    
    # Effect
    sizes = [abs(effect) * 500 for effect in data['Effect']]
    
    plt.scatter(data['Path'], data['Effect'], s=sizes, alpha=0.5)
    
    # 
    for i in range(len(data)):
        plt.text(data['Path'][i], data['Effect'][i], f"{data['Effect'][i]:.4f}", ha='center', va='bottom')
    
    # 
    plt.title(f'Mediation Effects Bubble Chart for {trait}', fontsize=16)
    plt.xlabel('Path', fontsize=14)
    plt.ylabel('Effect Size', fontsize=14)

    # PNG
    plt.savefig(save_path + f'/{trait}_mediation_effects_bubble_chart.png')
    
    # 
    plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot_mediation_effects_bubble(mediation_results, save_path):
    plt.figure(figsize=(5, 3)) # 
    colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'purple', 'orange'] # 
    
    for idx, (trait, results) in enumerate(mediation_results.items()):
        data = pd.DataFrame({
            'Path': ['a', 'b', "c'", 'Indirect (ab)', 'Total'],
            'Effect': [results['path_a'], results['path_b'], results['path_c_prime'],
                       results['indirect_effect'], results['total_effect']],
        })
        
        sizes = [abs(effect) * 500 for effect in data['Effect']]
        
        plt.scatter(data['Path'], data['Effect'], s=sizes, alpha=0.6, label=trait, color=colors[idx]) # alpha
        
        # 
        for i in range(len(data)):
            plt.text(data['Path'][i], data['Effect'][i], f"{data['Effect'][i]:.4f}", ha='center', va='bottom', color=colors[idx])

    # 
    plt.title('Mediation Effects Bubble Chart Comparison Across Traits', fontsize=12)
    plt.xlabel('Path', fontsize=6)
    plt.ylabel('Effect Size', fontsize=6)
    
    # 
    plt.legend()
    
    # 
    plt.savefig(save_path + '/mediation_effects_comparison_chart.png')
    
    # 
    plt.show()

save_location = 'D:/SINKY/Lecture/8001/data'
plot_mediation_effects_bubble(mediation_results, save_location)

def plot_mediation_effects_heatmap(mediation_results, save_path):
    traits = list(mediation_results.keys())
    paths = ['path_a', 'path_b', 'path_c_prime', 'indirect_effect', 'total_effect']
    heatmap_data = [[results[path] for path in paths] for trait, results in mediation_results.items()]
    
    df_map = pd.DataFrame(heatmap_data, index=traits, columns=paths)
    
    # 
    plt.figure(figsize=(5, 4))
    sns.heatmap(df_map, annot=True, fmt=".4f", cmap='coolwarm', linewidths=.5)
    
    plt.title('Mediation Effects Heatmap', fontsize=14)
    
    # 
    plt.savefig(save_path + '/mediation_effects_heatmap.png')
    
    # 
    plt.show()
